  <br/>
  <strong> <p>Tip 2</p></strong>
  <p>
  revert back to change number {N} - where N is a number in your undo list
  </p>
  <pre id='vimCodeElement'>
  :undo <span class="Delimiter">{</span>N<span class="Delimiter">}</span>
  </pre>
  <div class="span3 author">
    <p> <strong>Source: </strong> vim manual </p>
  </div>
  <br/>
  <strong> <p>Tip 3</p></strong>
  <p>
  Go to older text state {N} file writes before.
  When changes were made since the last write
  <code>:earlier 1f</code> will revert the text to the state when
  it was written.  Otherwise it will go to the write
  before that.  When at the state of the first file write, or when
  the file was not written, ":earlier 1f" will go to
  before the first change.
  </p>
  <pre id='vimCodeElement'>
  :earlier <span class="Delimiter">{</span>N<span class="Delimiter">}</span><span class="Identifier">f</span>
  </pre>
  <div class="span3 author">
    <p> <strong>Source: </strong> vim manual </p>
  </div>
  <br/>
  <strong> <p>Tip 4</p></strong>
  <p>
  Go to newer text state {N} file writes later.
  When at the state of the last file write, ":later 1f"
  will go to the newest text state.
  </p>
  <pre id='vimCodeElement'>
  :later <span class="Delimiter">{</span>N<span class="Delimiter">}</span><span class="Identifier">f</span>
  </pre>
  <div class="span3 author">
    <p> <strong>Source: </strong> vim manual </p>
  </div>
  <br/>
